      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Key features**\n- **One cationic center:** a **tertiary aliphatic ammonium** (`[NH+]` with three carbon substituents). This will be **positively charged at physiological pH** (strong hERG risk driver).\n- **Two aromatic rings:** two **phenyl** groups (hydrophobic/aromatic \u201canchors\u201d).\n- **Linkers:** one side has **\u2013CH2\u2013CH2\u2013O\u2013Ph** (ether-linked aryl), the other **\u2013CH2\u2013CH2\u2013Ph** (alkyl-linked aryl). Overall gives a **flexible, elongated** scaffold.\n- **Two sulfonamides on the rings:** `\u2013NS(=O)2CH3` (aryl sulfonamides). These are **strongly electron-withdrawing, polar**, and typically **not basic**; they add H-bonding capacity and increase PSA.",
